@startuml seq-markdown-render
'' ============================================================================
''
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: Markdown → render result (unified plus renderer-side
'' postprocessors) and its return into DataScript + the imperative innerHTML body.
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: the Markdown pipeline is an ordered chain best
'' shown as a self-call ladder on one lifeline, and the async boundary
'' (Promise `.then` / `.catch`) needs a return arrow that re-enters the re-frame
'' loop. PlantUML's nested activations + a `group` for the plugin chain express
'' both; Mermaid cannot nest the chain inside the async hop cleanly.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Render Markdown — `:markdown/render` fx → `:content/rendered`

autonumber "0:"

participant "re-frame fx\n`:markdown/render`" as Fx REFRAME_TINT
participant "renderer.markdown\n`render`" as MD MARKDOWN_TINT
participant "unified processor" as U MARKDOWN_TINT
participant "re-frame\nevents" as Ev REFRAME_TINT
participant "DataScript\nconn" as DS DATASCRIPT_TINT
participant "ui.views\nmarkdown-body" as UI RENDERER_TINT

Fx -> MD : `render text`
activate MD
MD -> U : normalize GitHub math escapes\nand build processor

group unified plugin chain (in order)
  U -> U : `remark-parse`   — Markdown → mdast
  U -> U : `remark-gfm`     — tables / strikethrough / tasklists
  U -> U : `remark-math`    — inline/display TeX placeholders
  U -> U : `remark-rehype`  — mdast → hast
  U -> U : `rehype-slug`    — stable heading ids (for TOC + find)
  U -> U : `rehype-highlight` — code-block syntax classes
  U -> U : `rehype-stringify` — hast → HTML string
  U -> U : `DOMParser`      — parse serialized HTML for replacements
  U -> U : `MathJax`        — TeX → SVG
  U -> U : `Mermaid`        — diagrams → SVG
  U -> U : `tree-sitter`    — fenced-code spans
end

U --> MD : HTML + TOC + asset metadata
MD --> Fx : Promise
deactivate MD

alt fulfilled
  Fx -> Ev : `.then` → dispatch\n`[:content/rendered path stamp result]`
  Ev -> DS : `:ds/transact {:doc/path :doc/html :doc/toc :doc/assets}`
  DS -> UI : `:doc/active` recomputes (via `:ds/rev`)
  UI -> UI : `did-update` → `set! innerHTML (:html result)`\n(**not** VDOM-diffed)
else rejected
  Fx -> Ev : `.catch` → dispatch\n`[:content/error {path message:"render error: …"}]`
  Ev -> DS : `:ds/transact {:doc/path :doc/error message}`
  DS -> UI : `content-view` shows `.vv-error`
end

note over MD, U
  Runs in the **renderer** (Chromium): the all-ESM remark/rehype
  stack bundles cleanly there. No `rehype-raw` in the chain ⟶
  raw HTML embedded in Markdown is **not** re-parsed/injected.
  MathJax and Mermaid SVG generation happen after stringification
  and before the preview DOM is committed.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#67B11D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| markdown / unified pipeline |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DataScript content cache |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer / UI |
  |<#E0211D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| (error branch text) |
endlegend
@enduml
